0.title: Allergy
dlg: Although colds and seasonal allergies may share some of the same symptoms, they are different things altogether. Common colds are caused by viruses, whereas seasonal allergies are immune system reaction triggered by exposure to an allergen.

Here are the rationale we used:

  • Allergy start all of a sudden because your body is reacting to something you inhaled.
  • Cold symptoms take time to develop as the cold virus is invading the nasal passages.
  • Allergy never include fever
  • Allergy never include severe body aches
  • Allergy rarely include sore throat until later when all the drainage might have irritated the throat area.

Allergies
due to pollens, dust, dander or mold will be discussed here.

Let's find out if you have allergies or if you may have a cold or something else.



Before you continue, our sponsor would like to share this message with you. We think you will find it useful. Take a look.

Colds take some time to develop while allergies start all of a sudden because your body's immune system is reacting to something you inhaled like pollens or dust.

Let's continue and see what rational we are using to differentiate an allergy from a cold situation.

dlg:

Cold symptoms usually start about 24 to 72 hours after you come in contact with the virus.

When the cold virus first enter your nose and sinuses, they respond by making a clear mucus to help wash the virus from these areas.
Your symptoms will depend on the type of cold virus that is attacking. After 2 or 3 days, the body fights back. This change the mucus color to white or yellow.

Most symptoms due to colds that is not complicated usually takes care of itself within 10 days.

Your goal would be to shorten the duration of the cold and reduce any complications.

Close

A cold can also lead to:

  • Ear infection
  • Bronchitis
  • Pneumonia
  • Inflammation of the sinuses.

A cold
is a viral infection of your nose, sinuses and throat.

Now, how do you know you have a cold and not something like allergy, flu, sinusitis and so on?

Well let's see what you are looking at.

Before we take care of this cold, kindly take a look at what our sponsors have to say here. We think you will find it useful.

20.header:
Did your symptoms develop gradually or quickly?

Gradually would mean starting with a scratchy or sore throat and gradually progressing to runny or stufy nose.

Quickly would mean the symptoms happened pretty fast.

21.header:
Quickly?
Probably looking at an allergy situation if it started quickly.

If you have sneezing or a runny nose and it started all of a sudden, then you may be looking at allergy rather than a cold. If it started gradually, then we may suspect a cold.

Would you like to see the allergy section or continue with cold?
Continuing with cold will assume it started gradually.
